Random Password Generator

Description

The Random Password Generator is a Python application developed as part of the Oasis Infobyte Python Programming Internship. It generates strong and secure random passwords based on user preferences.

Features

- Generate random passwords
- User-defined password length
- Supports uppercase letters
- Supports lowercase letters
- Supports numbers
- Supports special characters
- Input validation
- Generate multiple passwords without restarting the program

Technologies Used

- Python
- random module
- string module

How to Run

1. Open the project in Pydroid 3 or any Python IDE.
2. Run the "password_generator.py" file.
3. Enter the password length (minimum 8 characters).
4. Choose the character types.
5. The program generates a secure random password.

Project Structure

